          "testo":"The 'Rio Papa' originates from a spring in 'Le Gorghe' area, it passes through Vigo Meano up to Gazzadina. At the beginning of Val dei Molinari (Molinari Valley) it streams into Rio Cortesano, then it runs across Camparta Media and Camparta Bassa to reach San Lazzaro and finally flowing into the Avisio.<br>Along its course it creates pools, which are fundamental shelters for biodiversity, important breeding sites for various amphibian species, such as the common frog, the common toad and the fire salamander. <br>The stream is home to a particular species of invertebrate: the freshwater Shrimp (Austropotamobius pallipes). This is a rare species of crustacean, it is protected by the law as it is endangered and it can be considered an indicator of good water quality."
